                {
                    "id": "upstream_qualitative_low_corner",
                    "description": "Low corner of the upstream `COOxidation: Qualitative - Positive Production and Loss` 3Г—3Г—3 sweep (test_co_oxidation.jl:337-366): OH=1e11, HOв‚‚=1e13, NO=1e14, NOв‚‚=2e14 mвЃ»Ві (CO=2.5e18, Oв‚ѓ=1e18 at defaults). The upstream test asserts L_OH, L_HO2, L_HOx and HO2_ss are all strictly positive at every sweep point вЂ” pinned here at rel=1e-10 (L_OH=6.75e10, L_HO2=2.868e10, L_HOx=7.8e8, HO2_ss=7.407e13, all > 0). Note P_O3 is negative here (в€’1.92e10): at this very low NO the gross HOв‚‚+NO production cannot keep up with the OH+Oв‚ѓ and HOв‚‚+Oв‚ѓ ozone-loss channels, so the net Oв‚ѓ rate is destruction вЂ” a regime the upstream qualitative test does not constrain (it checks only the four loss/steady-state outputs).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"OH": 1.0e11, "HO2": 1.0e13, "NO": 1.0e14, "NO2": 2.0e14},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
