                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "oh_doubled_scales_oh_channels",
                    "description": "OH doubled to 2.0e12 mвЃ»Ві (2Г— default). L_OH is exactly linear in OH and doubles to 1.846e12. L_HOx gains only through its OH+NOв‚‚ term (the HOв‚‚ВІ term is OH-independent), rising to 5.58e11; chain_length therefore falls (the numerator is OH-independent, the denominator L_HOx grows). HO2_ss is linear in OH and doubles to 5.926e13. P_O3 drops slightly (its OH+Oв‚ѓ loss term grows with OH). L_HO2 has no OH dependence and is unchanged. Verifies the OH-linearity of L_OH and HO2_ss and the partial-OH dependence of L_HOx and P_O3.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"OH": 2.0e12},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
