            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "chain_length_vs_no2_regime_sweep",
                    "description": "HOx chain length and HOx termination rate as functions of NOв‚‚, swept logarithmically from 2.5e15 to 2.5e17 mвЃ»Ві (~0.1 to ~10 ppb at STP) with all other inputs at their defaults (CO=2.5e18, OH=1e12, HOв‚‚=1e14, NO=2.5e15, Oв‚ѓ=1e18). As NOв‚‚ rises the OH+NOв‚‚в†’HNOв‚ѓ termination accelerates: L_HOx grows while the gross propagation rate k_HO2_NOВ·HOв‚‚В·NO is unchanged, so chain_length falls. This is the within-component analog of S&P Figure 6.3 (docs/src/co_oxidation.md) вЂ” the transition from the low-NOx long-chain (NOx-limited) regime to the high-NOx short-chain (VOC-limited) regime.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "NO2",
                                "range": {"start": 2.5e15, "stop": 2.5e17, "count": 60, "scale": "log"}
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "chain_length_vs_no2",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "HOx chain length vs NOв‚‚ number density on log-log axes. Monotonically falling curve: higher NOв‚‚ accelerates OH+NOв‚‚ termination, shortening the catalytic chain from ~24 cycles at NOв‚‚=2.5e15 down through 1 and toward ~0.8 at NOв‚‚=2.5e17.",
                            "x": {"variable": "NO2", "label": "NOв‚‚ number density (mвЃ»Ві)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "chain_length", "label": "HOx chain length (dimensionless)"}
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "l_hox_vs_no2",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "HOx termination rate L_HOx vs NOв‚‚ number density. Rises with NOв‚‚ вЂ” the OH+NOв‚‚ termination term is linear in NOв‚‚ вЂ” while the HOв‚‚-self-reaction term stays fixed; the growing termination rate is what drives the chain-length decline.",
                            "x": {"variable": "NO2", "label": "NOв‚‚ number density (mвЃ»Ві)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "L_HOx", "label": "HOx termination rate L_HOx (mвЃ»ВіВ·sвЃ»В№)"}
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "o3_production_vs_no_sweep",
                    "description": "Net ozone production rate and high-NOx HOв‚‚ steady state as functions of NO, swept logarithmically from 2.5e14 to 2.5e16 mвЃ»Ві (~0.01 to ~1 ppb at STP) with all other inputs at their defaults. The gross-production term k_HO2_NOВ·HOв‚‚В·NO is linear in NO so P_O3 rises with NO (and goes net-negative at the low-NO end where the fixed Oв‚ѓ-loss terms dominate). HO2_ss = k_CO_OHВ·COВ·OH/(k_HO2_NOВ·NO) is inversely proportional to NO, so it falls as NO rises вЂ” the more NO available, the faster HOв‚‚ is consumed and the lower its high-NOx steady state.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "NO",
                                "range": {"start": 2.5e14, "stop": 2.5e16, "count": 60, "scale": "log"}
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "p_o3_vs_no",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Net Oв‚ѓ production rate P_O3 vs NO number density. Rises with NO вЂ” the gross HOв‚‚+NO production term is linear in NO вЂ” crossing from net destruction (negative) at low NO to net production at higher NO once the propagation term overtakes the fixed OH+Oв‚ѓ and HOв‚‚+Oв‚ѓ ozone-loss terms.",
                            "x": {"variable": "NO", "label": "NO number density (mвЃ»Ві)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "P_O3", "label": "Net Oв‚ѓ production rate P_O3 (mвЃ»ВіВ·sвЃ»В№)"}
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "ho2_ss_vs_no",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "High-NOx HOв‚‚ steady state HO2_ss vs NO number density on log-log axes. Falls as 1/NO (HO2_ss = k_CO_OHВ·COВ·OH/(k_HO2_NOВ·NO)) вЂ” a straight line of slope -1 вЂ” since more NO drains HOв‚‚ faster.",
                            "x": {"variable": "NO", "label": "NO number density (mвЃ»Ві)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "HO2_ss", "label": "HOв‚‚ steady-state concentration (mвЃ»Ві)"}
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "hox_termination_vs_ho2_sweep",
                    "description": "HOx and HOв‚‚ loss rates as functions of the HOв‚‚ radical concentration, swept logarithmically from 1e13 to 1e15 mвЃ»Ві with all other inputs at their defaults. The HOв‚‚ self-reaction term twoВ·k_HO2_HO2В·HOв‚‚ВІ is quadratic in HOв‚‚ while the OH+NOв‚‚ term of L_HOx is HOв‚‚-independent, so L_HOx crosses over from NHL-dominated (OH+NOв‚‚ termination) at low HOв‚‚ to HHL-dominated (HOв‚‚ self-reaction) at high HOв‚‚. This is the within-component analog of the HHL/NHL crossover in S&P Figure 6.4 panel (c).",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "HO2",
                                "range": {"start": 1.0e13, "stop": 1.0e15, "count": 50, "scale": "log"}
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "l_hox_vs_ho2",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "HOx termination rate L_HOx vs HOв‚‚ number density on log-log axes. Flat at the OH+NOв‚‚ floor (~2.5e11) at low HOв‚‚, then rising as the quadratic HOв‚‚-self-reaction term overtakes it вЂ” the NHLв†’HHL termination crossover.",
                            "x": {"variable": "HO2", "label": "HOв‚‚ number density (mвЃ»Ві)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "L_HOx", "label": "HOx termination rate L_HOx (mвЃ»ВіВ·sвЃ»В№)"}
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "l_ho2_vs_ho2",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "HOв‚‚ loss rate L_HO2 vs HOв‚‚ number density on log-log axes. Rises monotonically, steepening from the linear HOв‚‚+NO and HOв‚‚+Oв‚ѓ channels toward the quadratic HOв‚‚-self-reaction channel at high HOв‚‚.",
                            "x": {"variable": "HO2", "label": "HOв‚‚ number density (mвЃ»Ві)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "L_HO2", "label": "HOв‚‚ loss rate L_HO2 (mвЃ»ВіВ·sвЃ»В№)"}
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "chain_length_heatmap_no_no2",
                    "description": "HOx chain length as a joint function of NO and NOв‚‚ (2-D log-log sweep), surfacing the NOx-regime structure of the catalytic cycle. NO в€€ [2.5e14, 2.5e16] mвЃ»Ві Г— NOв‚‚ в€€ [2.5e15, 2.5e17] mвЃ»Ві, with CO/OH/HOв‚‚/Oв‚ѓ at their defaults. chain_length = k_HO2_NOВ·HOв‚‚В·NO / (k_OH_NO2В·OHВ·NOв‚‚ + twoВ·k_HO2_HO2В·HOв‚‚ВІ): the numerator rises with NO while the denominator rises with NOв‚‚, so the high-chain-length corner is high NO / low NOв‚‚ (NOx-limited long-chain regime) and the low-chain-length corner is low NO / high NOв‚‚ (VOC-limited short-chain regime).",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "NO",
                                "range": {"start": 2.5e14, "stop": 2.5e16, "count": 25, "scale": "log"}
                            },
                            {
                                "parameter": "NO2",
                                "range": {"start": 2.5e15, "stop": 2.5e17, "count": 20, "scale": "log"}
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "chain_length_heatmap",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "HOx chain length as a function of (NO, NOв‚‚) on log-log axes. The lower-right region (high NO, low NOв‚‚) is the high-chain-length NOx-limited regime; the upper-left region (low NO, high NOв‚‚) is the low-chain-length VOC-limited regime where NOx termination cuts the catalytic cycle short.",
                            "x": {"variable": "NO", "label": "NO number density (mвЃ»Ві, log)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "NO2", "label": "NOв‚‚ number density (mвЃ»Ві, log)"},
                            "value": {"variable": "chain_length", "reduce": "final"}
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
